A. PROBLEM STATEMENT :

Design a Low-Level Design for a Parking Lot System.

Requirements:

The parking lot has multiple floors.
Each floor has parking spots of different types: Motorcycle (Two-wheeler), Compact (Car), and Large (Bus/Truck).
Different vehicle types can only park in compatible spots (e.g., a bus cannot park in a compact spot, but a bike can park anywhere).
On entry: Automatically assign the nearest available compatible parking spot and issue a ticket.
On exit: Calculate parking fee based on duration and vehicle type, then free up the spot.
Support basic operations: park vehicle, exit vehicle, check availability, and display status.

Constraints:

In-memory implementation is acceptable.
Assume a medium-sized parking lot (3–5 floors).
Support multiple vehicles entering/exiting concurrently (mention thread-safety as future improvement).

B. HAPPY PATH STORY (SIMPLE REAL LIFE STORY)

=> Rahul drives his Car into the parking lot.
=> The system checks from Floor 1 upwards and finds the nearest available Compact spot on Floor 1.
It assigns the spot and issues a Ticket with entry time.
=> After 4 hours, Rahul returns. The system calculates the fee (₹20 per hour for Car = ₹80),
prints the amount, frees the parking spot, and closes the ticket.
=> Meanwhile, a bike rider gets a Motorcycle spot on Floor 2, and a bus gets a Large spot on Floor 3.
=> This flow covers vehicle entry, spot allocation by type, ticketing, fee calculation, and spot release.

C. 6 MANDATORY STEPS FOR LLD DESIGN

1. Clarify requirements

=> Functional: Multi-floor support, different spot & vehicle types,
automatic nearest spot allocation, ticket generation, fee calculation on exit.
=> Non-Functional: Fast spot finding, support concurrent operations.
=> Assumptions: Simple hourly pricing, single parking lot instance, no reserved/handicapped spots.
=> Edge Cases: Parking full, no compatible spot available, invalid ticket, negative parking duration.

2. Identify Entities & Relationships

=> Main Entities: ParkingLot, Floor, ParkingSpot, Vehicle, Ticket, ParkingFeeCalculator
=> Key Relationships:
ParkingLot has multiple Floors (Composition)
Floor has multiple ParkingSpots (Composition)
ParkingSpot can hold one Vehicle (Association)

